data-triple-N3.o: "Palaeography or Palaeography, also spelt paleography (from Greek παλαιός palaios, "old" and γράφειν graphein, "to write") is the study of ancient writing. Included in the discipline is the practice of deciphering, reading, and dating historical manuscripts, and the cultural context of writing, including the methods with which writing and books were produced, and the history of scriptoria."@en
